Reasoning: The paper discusses the characteristics and limitations of DataCite as a bibliometric data source for analyzing scholarly production of open data. The paper touches upon issues related to metadata incompleteness, lack of standardization, and ambiguous definitions of several fields, which are relevant to the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), cybersecurity (cs.CY), cryptography (cs.CR), and databases (cs.DB).
